HEADWORD: Miscellaneous
<hw>Mis`cel*la"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>miscellaneus</ets> mixed, miscellaneous, fr. <ets>miscellus</ets>
mixed, fr. <ets>miscere</ets> to mix. See <er>Mix</er>, and cf.
<er>Miscellany</er>.]</ety> <def>Mixed; mingled; consisting of several
things; of diverse sorts; promiscuous; heterogeneous; <as>as, a
<ex>miscellaneous</ex> collection</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>miscellaneous</xex> rabble.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Mis`cel*la"ne*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Mis`cel*la"ne*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miscellanist</ent>⟦br⟧
